    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-04-11T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-04-11T16:00:00-05:00" n="635"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/17813</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Collector <persName type="from">Cobb</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">El Paso</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-04-11T14:00:00-07:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1916, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A mining company which has been shipping fuel regularly to Chihuahua informs me
                    confidentially of their inability to get movement south from Juarez during past
                    week. Juarez authorities have told them shipping could proceed as soon as train
                    crew could come in from Chihuahua. Three crews have arrived but have not become
                    available for southern shipping. It appears that Juarez authorities are holding
                    crew for some unknown military use of their own, possibly that they might not be
                    available about Chihuahua.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cobb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
